definitions.definition: (of an action, activity, or piece of work) having been completed or ended.
examples: a preparatory drawing for the finished painting

definitions.definition: (of a person) having completed or ended an action or activity.
examples: they'll be finished here in an hour

definitions.definition: having lost effectiveness, power, or prestige.
examples: he was told he was finished at the club

definitions.definition: (of an object or room) having been given a particular decorative surface as the final stage in its manufacture or decoration.
(of livestock) having completed fattening before slaughter.
examples: a reduction in prices for finished cattle

definitions.definition: bring (a task or activity) to an end; complete.
examples: they were straining to finish the job
synonyms: put the finishing touches to; accomplish
polish off "Mrs. Porter had just finished the task"completed

definitions.definition: consume or get through the final amount or portion of (something, especially food or drink).
examples: finish your fajita while it's still hot
synonyms: run through; informaldown "Hitch finished his dinner"

definitions.definition: (of an activity) come to an end.
examples: the war has finished but nothing has changed

definitions.definition: have no more need for or nothing more to do with.
reach the end of a race or other sporting competition, typically in a particular position.
examples: she finished third in the 3-meter springboard diving

definitions.definition: complete the manufacture or decoration of (a material, object, or place) by giving it an attractive surface appearance.
examples: the interior was finished with V-jointed American oak
synonyms: glaze "some items were finished in a black lacquer"

definitions.definition: complete the fattening of (livestock) before slaughter.
prepare (a girl) for entry into fashionable society.
